		<hr size="1">Well, that's an interesting question.  The points board can be manipulated, I think - at least, I saw a post once by someone claiming to know how to do that. The negative points were supposed to frustrate griefing, but instead for a lot of folks, it promotes it - if you don't care about being the top PvPer, who cares if you bind-camp some 15th level snot?</P><P>It's interesting to look at the page from time to time, but I don't think that at an individual level people pay much attention to it.  At a collective - guild - level, it's still useful.  Nice to see when your guild makes the top ten or twenty for the day. <br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
